              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>For any type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> we have a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I/" title="Proposition" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {toProp}\,{A}]]></fr:tex> equipped with a unit map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta _{\mathsf {prop}}\colon  A \to \mathsf {toProp}\,{A}]]></fr:tex>; moreover, we have the following induction principle: for any family of <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H/" title="Contractible type" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H" type="local">propositions</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\colon  \mathsf {toProp}\,A \to  \mathsf {Prop}]]></fr:tex>, any function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\colon  \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
